<h1>The PMOG Toolbar</h1>
<h5>Commencing and Extending Your PMOG Play</h5> 

<br />
<div class="help">

<dl>
<dt>Installation</dt>
	<dd>Lacking a PMOG extension?  Check out our <a href="/help/install">Installation Help Page</a> to download and install a fresh copy of PMOG.</dd>

<dt>Updates</dt>
	<dd><div id="extension_version"></div>
<%= render :partial => 'shared/extension_detection' %>  Why bother upgrading?  What is new with PMOG?  Check the <a href="/about/versions">PMOG Version History Page</a> for a release history of the PMOG toolbar.</dd>

<a name="keyboardshortcuts"></a><dt>Keyboard Shortcuts</dt>

	<dd>Lay Mines, close Portals, send messages in a jiff!  The PMOG toolbar supports the pressing of keys on your keyboard for common PMOG commands.  For example, control+alt+H will hide or show your toolbar. See our <a href="/help/keycommands">Key Commands Page</a> for more details.</dd>

<a name="hidingpmog"></a><dt>Hiding PMOG</dt>

	<dd>You can make PMOG go away, be hidden, if you click the small P in the lower right corner of your browser window, in your status bar:</dd>
	
	<center><img src="/images/help/toolbar-hide-corner.png" alt="hiding the PMOG toolbar" width="333" height="129"></center>
	
	<dd>Clicking that button shown above will toggle your PMOG toolbar hidden or visible.  That button appears in the Firefox "status bar" which can be turned on and off.  If you've hidden PMOG and you can't get it back, try the hide/show keyboard shortcut: control+alt+H</dd>
	
<a name="contentqualitythreshold"></a><dt>Cutting down on PMOG Events</dt>

	<dd>Are you seeing too many Portals and Missions everywhere?  You can turn the number of Missions and Portals you see through your PMOG preferences.</dd>
	
	<dd>Open your preferences from the P menu on the left side of your PMOG toolbar.  There you can control a number of things about PMOG, including the "Content Quality Threshold" - here's a picture of the toolbar on the right, and the preferences window on the left:</dd>
	
	<center><img src="/images/help/contentqualitypreferences.jpg" alt="Content Quality Preferences settings" border="0" width="450" height="262" /></center>
	
	<dd>The higher that number is, between 1 and 5, the fewer PMOG Portals and Missions you will see.  We recommend 4 as a good way to see the best of the best.  5 is just about nothing!  And 1 is everything, low and high rated.</dd>

<a name="changingtheskin"></a><dt>Changing the Skin</dt>

	<dd>For some players, the default wood skin ("classic") is hard to read, or doesn't render right in their browser.  For those people, and players who like less stimulation, we have the "plain" skin.  You can select it from editing your settings on your player profile, or by altering your preferences in your browser.  Change your skin from classic to plain, and you can have a PMOG toolbar that looks like this:</dd>
	
	<dd><a href="http://skitch.com/justinreach/8jkb/a-version-history-of-pmog"><img src="http://img.skitch.com/20080306-fyim941t3rhwngs356mxy7rdet.preview.jpg" alt="A Version History of PMOG" /></a></dd>
	
	<dd>To change your skin preferences, go to the P icon on the left side of the toolbar.  Choose "preferences" from that menu that pops up, and select the "Extension Skin" that you want: plain or classic.  If you are having trouble reading PMOG bits in your toolbar, plain is probably the way to go.</dd>

<dt>Login Issues</dt>

	<dd>Are you unable to login to the extension?  Check our <a href="/help/login">Login Help Page</a>.</dd>

<dt>Incompatibilities</dt>
	<dd>Some things make PMOG not work: Google Gears, for example.  AdBlockPlus seems to prevent our events from showing up.  We're working to fix PMOG to play with everything!  Keep an eye on <a href="/about/versions">our version history</a> to see if we fix your problem.</dd>
	
<dt>NoScript</dt>
	<dd>PMOG can be made to work with the Firefox extension "NoScript" - here are some <a href="http://pmog.com/forums/gameplay/topics/using-noscript-with-pmog">instructions on the Forums</a> and a <a href="http://pmog.com/missions/using_noscript_with_pmog">helpful Mission</a>, from our player <a href="/users/barril">barril</a>.</dd>
	
