<dt>Playing Across the Web</dt>

	<dd>So, now, how do you play PMOG?  Ignore everything here, continue on your web browsing.  Once in a while, glance at your score.  Maybe click on a tool.  Or wait for a tool to click on you!</dd>
	
	<dd>If you see something like this pop up in your browser:</dd>
	
	<center><img src="/images/help/event-crates.png" alt="event: crates have landed!" border="0" /></center>
	
	<br />
	
	<dd>That's a <b>PMOG message</b>, you have another PMOG player to thank for whatever tool was just triggered.</dd>
	
	<dd>You can play along with them by clicking on something in your toolbar, or visiting <b>http://pmog.com</b> once in a while.</dd>
	
<dt>More Help</dt>

<dd>Take your time and experiment with the PMOG toolbar... learn its secrets!  You can't break the internet by poking at buttons on PMOG.  Maybe try <% if logged_in? %>
the <a href="/learn">PMOG tutorial</a>, or, see <% end %><a href="/help">our help page</a> if you're stuck!</dd>
